quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  26,61,"And when the two hosts saw each other, the companions of Musa said: \"We are sure to be overtaken"
  26,62,"(Musa) said: \"Nay, verily with me is my Lord. He will guide me"
  26,63,"Then We revealed to Musa (saying): \"Strike the sea with your stick.\" And it parted, and each separate part became like huge mountain"
  26,64,Then We brought near the others to that place
  26,65,And We saved Musa and all those with him
  26,66,Then We drowned the others
  26,67,"Verily, in this is indeed a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,68,"And verily your Lord, He is truly the All-Mighty, the Most Merciful"
  26,69,And recite to them the story of Ibrahim
  26,70,"When he said to his father and his people: \"What do you worship"
  26,71,"They said: \"We worship idols, and to them we are ever devoted"
  26,72,"He said: \"Do they hear you when you call"
  26,73,Or do they benefit you or do they cause harm
  26,74,"They said: \"(Nay) but we found our fathers doing so"
  26,75,"He said: \"Do you observe that which you have been worshipping"
  26,76,You and your ancient fathers
  26,77,"Verily, they are enemies to me, save the Lord of Al-`Alamin"
  26,78,"Who has created me, and it is He Who guides me"
  26,79,And it is He Who feeds me and gives me to drink
  26,80,"And when I am ill, it is He Who cures me"
  26,81,"And Who will cause me to die, and then will bring me to life"
  26,82,"And Who, I hope, will forgive me my faults on the Day of Recompense"
  26,83,"My Lord! Bestow Hukm on me, and join me with the righteous"